review_blob: Bottle. Scent of maltiness and chocolate, with a hint of smoke. Lighter bodied porter, flavors of coffee and malty sweetness with a relatively clean finish. Lighter than I would have liked, but it is serviceable.

This beer is not for the week of heart. Its a real kick in the pants. Absolutely pitch black, malty sweetness evident in the flavor, surprising considering the alcohol is very prevalent. Tastes of roasted malts and coffee, a full, thick and complex brew that is not for everyone.

Bottle. Sweet caramel and maltiness on the scent, the flavor seems to come though in the same way, a little more bitter than I was expecting. Not overly malty, but certainly more malty than hoppy. Solid mouthfeel. A bit of spice at the end, overall this is a tasty brew.
Pours a hazy tan with little head, aroma of faint citrus, with a bit of zest. Extremely drinkable beer, good for a casual summertime, not remarkably memorable however. Tastes of lemons and oranges.

Poured from a 22 oz. bomber, this is not something Id ordinarily try. Poured a thick red with a negligible maroon head, the brew is certainly tarty and fruity, and also sweet. I  have to stop at one of these, it is much too sweet for me. However, it is a great beer to try and I enjoyed it.
